        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/10–2)46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Durbrow</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-17T16:00:00-05:00">October 17, 1946—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1844. Dept’s 1651 Sept 13. Pls inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    French Govt has now replied favorably re abolition Alcorn Italy<note n="57" xml:id="d580fn57">Telegram 4933, October 2, from Paris, conveyed the message
                        of the French favorable reply (740.00119 Control (Italy)/10–246).</note> and
                    Dept is therefore anxious obtain <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> reply
                    soonest possible.<note n="58" xml:id="d580fn58">In telegram 3906, October 19,
                        from Moscow, Mr. Durbrow reported that on October 17 he had sent a letter to
                        Dekanozov giving the substance of this telegram. On October 18 he was told
                        that the matter was under consideration and that a decision could be
                        expected soon. (740.00119 Control (Italy)/10–1946)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
